OL,3,CUnions look to improved employment
OL,4,Crelations under a Labour government
OL,6,FHundreds of thousands of workers,
OL,7,Fincluding nurses, junior doctors,
OL,8,Fteachers, train drivers, barristers,
OL,9,Fcivil servants, council staff and
OL,10,Funiversity lecturers, have taken
OL,11,Findustrial action since June 2022,
OL,12,Fseen as the start of the period of
OL,13,Findustrial unrest.
OL,15,FMany of the disputes were sparked by
OL,16,Frising inflation and the impact of the
OL,17,Fcost-of-living crisis.
